VENDORING PATH (decision recorded per topos-temporal-video-encoder/tasks.md 1.2/1.3)
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

Path (a) was chosen: a LITERAL, VERBATIM vendor of the upstream modeling source
at the pinned commit above. Unlike danijar/dreamerv3 (a research-infra tangle
that forced a faithful re-implementation, path b), InternVideo-Next ships a
self-contained set of modeling files that import only public PyPI libraries
(torch, einops, timm, flash_attn, easydict, numpy). The right vendor is therefore
the upstream files themselves, byte-for-byte, so the in-repo copy diffs cleanly
against the hub at the pinned revision and is auditable forever.

Vendored files (byte-identical to the pinned upstream revision):
  - modeling_internvideo_next.py   (encoder: PatchEmbed, Attention/FlashAttention,
                                    Block, InternVideoNextBackbone, the
                                    InternVideoNext PreTrainedModel wrapper, and
                                    the AttentionPoolingBlock head)
  - modeling_config.py             (InternVideoNextConfig PretrainedConfig subclass)
  - config.json                    (encoder-only config; auto_map points at the
                                    two files above)
  - preprocessor_config.json       (VideoMAE image-processor settings, res 224)

The upstream source files are kept BYTE-IDENTICAL — no SPDX headers are injected
into them — precisely so the provenance diff against the hub stays clean. The
SPDX identifier and MIT attribution live here in UPSTREAM and in __init__.py
instead. `model.safetensors` (~182 MB, fp16, 91M params) is NOT vendored into
git; it is fetched once at setup time into a git-ignored local dir
(state/models/internvideo_next_base_p14_res224_f16/) by
`kaine/setup/internvideo_next.py`.

WHY VENDOR (security): the upstream repo declares `auto_map` in config.json, so
`AutoModel.from_pretrained(..., trust_remote_code=True)` would download and
EXECUTE this Python from the hub at load time — a supply-chain execution path
that conflicts with KAINE's local-only / no-cloud posture and would weaken the
"frozen encoder gives an attacker no foothold" property. Vendoring the reviewed
source once, pinning the revision, and loading with `trust_remote_code=False`
against a LOCAL directory removes that path entirely: no code is fetched or
executed from the hub at runtime. See
kaine/modules/topos/internvideo_next_loader.py and design.md §5.

The Predictor "P" and Decoder "D" of InternVideo-Next's Encoder-Predictor-Decoder
are training-time apparatus and are NOT distributed in this published checkpoint
(verified: a single encoder-only model.safetensors, no predictor/decoder class,
config, or weights). Only the frozen encoder is used. See design.md §8.

